key_findings: N=1 is already optimal at 45 degrees (score 0.6612)
All gradient-based approaches found ZERO improvement
Fresh start configurations are much worse than baseline
The baseline is at an extremely strong local optimum
notes: Gradient-based density flow optimization tested multiple approaches: numerical gradient descent, physics simulation with spring forces, fresh start configurations (hexagonal, spiral, grid), and exhaustive N=1 optimization. NONE found any improvement over the baseline. The baseline is already at a very strong local optimum with ~70% packing efficiency. The gap to target (1.44 points) requires fundamentally different approaches that we have not yet discovered.
